node.text:
Yesterday I shown the team a video of my beautiful little baby Azaylia and it not only broke my heart, but completely broke my spirit. I not only didn’t want to be on this ride, but I didn’t want to be on this earth. I was nearly weak enough yesterday to give up completely. 💔

But I looked up to the sky and found my inner Azaylia. I realised that if I don’t give it my all and leave everything on this earth, I will never earn the right to make it through those gates of heaven to be with her again. 🙏🏾

So through the hurt, cold, wind, rain and hills I told myself… “I am a Beast, I am a Lion, I am Hercules, I am Thor and it’s time to put the hammer down on this shit!” 🦁⚡️🔨

Let’s Go Champ! 😤

node.text:
To everyone who has a father in heaven, my thoughts are with you. To all the fathers who have a child in heaven, my heart is with you. 🧡

Lots of love and respect to all the amazing fathers out there. Dads, if you feel like you aren’t doing enough, you’re probably right. Being simply present in your child’s life is not enough. Invest your time, your feelings, your knowledge, your happiness, your strength, your wisdom, your trust, your support and your whole hearted love in them. Nurture them, guide them, teach them. BE YOUR CHILDS HERO... & one day they’ll turn out to be yours! 🙌🏾

My Champion. My Hero. My Inspiration.  My Baby. - Azaylia Diamond Cain 👼🏼

#fathersday

node.text:
Last night, I was scrolling through some photos and videos for hours as I couldn’t sleep with today pending...

One of the things that I miss the most about Azaylia, is our sleepovers at the hospital. The feeling when I woke up next to her in the morning, drew the blinds and seen her beautiful face with that incredible smile was magical. The fact I’d been gifted another day with the love of my life, when no day was promised, was euphoric and indescribable. ✨

First thing, we used to set the tempo for the rest of the day. It was important to start the day off right with positive vibes, good energy and endless amounts of appreciation. Despite what Azaylia was going through, she would ALWAYS greet me with the most overwhelming energy and stunning smile, which gave me all the strength and courage I needed to fuel my mind, heart and spirits through another day battling by her side. 💯

Azaylia seemed to be able to lift the spirits of anyone in her presence and especially me because of her sheer strength, great hearted bravery and beautifully bright ora. When I thought I had to be strong for her, it turned out she was the source of my strength. When I thought I needed to be brave for her, she was the reason for my courage. When I thought she needed to see me smiling and positive, she was always my inspiration. & when I thought I needed to give it 100 to fight by her side everyday, she was already giving 120! 🦁

If I could pick any 8 months of my life to relive, it would begin on the 10.08.20. Azaylia made the hardest and most devastating time any parent could go through, without question, the BEST days of my life! A time where I’d give up the remaining years of mine in a split second, to experience it with her again. ❤️

Azaylia Diamond Cain - You’re the most amazing daughter any daddy could wish for and I miss you so much. Even though my heart is broken beyond repair, I feel incredibly blessed to be your daddy and HONOURED to be lucky enough to to call you my daughter. You changed my life, you saved my life and you MADE my life. I LOVE YOU CHAMP - MY HERO! 👼🏼🧡 #AzayliaDiamondCain #FathersDay #DaddysGirl

node.text:
The week leading up to Azaylia’s day was comprised of sadness, fear and anxiety. I was sad because my beautiful baby had passed, I was scared because it was our final goodbye and I was anxious because I wanted to make sure I had the strength to stand up and speak about my hero, and how she impacted my life. ❤️

I wrote a speech at 4am two days before Azaylia’s day. I couldn’t bring myself to go back to it or read through because of the pain it caused. I was so nervous that I wouldn’t have the strength when I came to it, and It made me panic, as it meant everything to me to be able to speak about my likkle lion that day. But when the day came, I just had some strong belief and some crazy faith, that my baby would get me through it. And like always, she did. 🥲

To the top of every mountain, to the bottom of every valley. Along every road, across every ocean. North to south, east to west, corner to corner, pillar to post. I’ll take you there. 👼🏼

Let’s Go Champ! 🧡
“Oobee doo, I wanna be like you!”
#AzayliaDiamondCain

node.text:
Today was supposed to be a day of unquestionable happiness. However, it turned out like most days on this journey; A miracle blindsided by heartbreak! 😢💔
.
We got told a few days ago that’s Azaylia would be ringing the bell today and coming home with us, as a family to resume treatment 2 days per week as an outpatient. However, 10 minutes before the moment we have been praying for over the last 5 months... We got urgently informed that Azaylia’s leukemia had returned. We crumbled and cancelled the celebration as we felt broken and numb to the core before seeing her beautiful face telling us, the show must go on and us then realising how far our little girl has come and howmuch she deserves this moment. She has battled against the odds, she has overcome every obstacle in her path and she has done it all with remarkable spirit and the biggest smile on her face! 🥲❤️
.
For now we are enjoying precious moments at home until we return to hospital on Friday! Thank you for your support and please keep our beautiful daughter in your prayers! 🙏🏾❤️

Yesterday was World Cancer Day. A day that 6 months ago I probably wouldn’t have known anything about or had a connection to. However, since my daughter got diagnosed with AML leukaemia, it is something close to my heart and I have been working hard to raise as much awareness as possible since!
.
Many parents are unaware that they can donate their umbilical cord after giving birth. Also, many hospitals do not offer the service to do so. Being a parent of a baby girl that has been given a second chance at life because of an umbilical cord, I find this sad and I want to do everything within my power to raise awareness to as many parents as I can and help provide the services for all hospitals to cater for this!
.
Please save this video, share this video and spread this message far and wide! 🌍 Let’s raise awareness and make a step in the right direction to save as many poorly children/adults as we can! ❤️ @anthonynolancharity @dkms_uk
.
(Link In Bio) to join the stem cell register with a few clicks 🙌🏾
.
 #worldcancerday #cancer #cancerawareness #childhoodcancer #leukemia #leukemiaawareness

No gym, no facilities, no fancy camera... Just a hotel room, hard work and a dream! 💭 720 reps / 45 minute skip in the 🏦 
.
My dream... Once my beautiful daughter Azaylia has won her fight against leukemia, is to FIGHT 2-3 times per year for children’s cancer. Donating my fight purses and raising awareness for this incredible cause. ✊🏾
.
Because of this, I am putting aside all the excuses I could have... & maximising what I do have so when the time comes... I am in shape and ready to go with minimal delay! 😤
.
Don’t dwell on the negatives... Find a positive, set a goal and GET AT IT! 💯
.

node.text:
I would like to thank everyone who has supported us throughout this 1070 mile ride. Everyone who has sent kind messages, shared the journey, turned out to welcome us in, shouted let’s go champ out of their car windows and donated to such an important cause. 

I would also like to thank you for keeping my daughter in your hearts, speaking her name and supporting us to continue the amazing legacy that she left behind which will help so many children fighting cancer moving forward. 

This journey has never been about me and I don’t want, need or seek any credit. I am honoured to devote my life to this cause, blessed to have been chosen to be my daughters father and grateful for the support @theazayliafoundation has received.

I want each and every person to know how important you are, how valuable your efforts have been and how much you are needed in this journey going forward.

This is just the beginning. Let’s Go Champ! 🦁🧡

Storm-Breaker ⛈

Day 14 - The last 87 miles of this 1000+ mile journey from the bottom of England to the top of Scotland. 🏴󠁧󠁢󠁥󠁮󠁧󠁿🏴󠁧󠁢󠁳󠁣󠁴󠁿

From north to south, east to west, I’ll take you there baby. 🧭

Thank you for all of your support this far. To our pride, please give us one last push in raising awareness and donating to get us over the line today. 🧡

LET’S GO CHAMP! 🦁
@theazayliafoundation 

To donate 👉🏾 Link in bio

node.text:
All I wanted from yesterday was Azaylia to be able to point down from heaven and tell her friends “THATS MY DADDY!” 🦁

We endured 16 miles and 6,000+ feet of raw climbing on our 65 mile route through the Cairngorm mountains which took us to 850 miles in 13 days. ⛰🛣 

It was by far the hardest physical challenge of my life. Blood, sweat, tears and a lot of sick got left on those mountains… But we made it! 🩸😰😭🤮

That ones for you CHAMP, I love you! 🧡 @theazayliafoundation

node.text:
Yesterday I shown the team a video of my beautiful little baby Azaylia and it not only broke my heart, but completely broke my spirit. I not only didn’t want to be on this ride, but I didn’t want to be on this earth. I was nearly weak enough yesterday to give up completely. 💔

But I looked up to the sky and found my inner Azaylia. I realised that if I don’t give it my all and leave everything on this earth, I will never earn the right to make it through those gates of heaven to be with her again. 🙏🏾

So through the hurt, cold, wind, rain and hills I told myself… “I am a Beast, I am a Lion, I am Hercules, I am Thor and it’s time to put the hammer down on this shit!” 🦁⚡️🔨

Let’s Go Champ! 😤

node.text:
10 days and 762 miles and we have reached SCOTLAND 🏴󠁧󠁢󠁳󠁣󠁴󠁿

This is a journey that I wouldn’t have considered in a car, never mind a push bike. But it feels amazing that I have taken my daughter from the bottom of the south coast of England, both visited places we would’ve never seen before for the first time, to breaching the Scottish boarders to the beautiful city of Edinburgh. 🥲

We have raised so much awareness already for childhood cancer, we have raised life saving funds, but this journey is not over until we have reached the highest point of the scotch border. 🦁

Thank you for all of your support, please continue and keep my beautiful daughter in your hearts. 🧡

To donate - Click the link in my bio 🙏🏾

node.text:
A huge part of this journey was about finding who I am, what I am capable of and how hard I can push myself for what I deeply care about. Putting myself through mental and physical stress and hardship on a daily basis, pushing my boundaries and getting out of my comfort zone to become comfortable with the uncomfortable, uncommon amongst the common and condition my head, my body and my heart to achieve greatness. 🦁

Any chance I get with the sea, whether foggy, hot or cold, light or dark I take it. It is a chance for me to refresh, revitalise and centralise myself in the present so I can be at one with myself and my daughter to remember, reminisce and realise why I am who I am and why I am on this mission. 🧡

I love you champ, from North to South, East to West… I’ll take you there baby! 👼🏼
